entries.title: Crypto exchange Gemini lays off 10% of workforce in its latest round of cuts
entries.description: Crypto exchange Gemini will reduce headcount by 10%, a spokesperson told CNBC on Monday.

entries.title: McDonald's accidentally gave a customer $5,000 in cash. He went viral on TikTok after returning it
entries.description: Josiah Vargas says he was picking up his Sausage McMuffin sandwich when he realized that the employee at the window had given him more than he ordered.

entries.title: Amazon expands air cargo service to India even as company cuts costs
entries.description: Amazon is expanding its in-house logistics arm even as CEO Andy Jassy looks to cut costs elsewhere inside the company.

entries.title: Microsoft announces multibillion-dollar investment in ChatGPT-maker OpenAI
entries.description: Microsoft announced a new multiyear, multibillion-dollar investment with the artificial intelligence lab OpenAI, according to a release Monday.

entries.title: Spotify cuts 6% of its workforce — read the memo CEO Daniel Ek sent to staff
entries.description: Spotify announced it is cutting 6% of its global workforce, as the music streaming giant contends with a gloomy economic environment.

entries.title: Bitcoin's 2023 rally gathers steam as cryptocurrency briefly tops $23,000
entries.description: The No. 1 token's price briefly topped $23,000 for the first time since Aug. 19, 2022, according to data from CoinGecko.

entries.title: Apple wants to manufacture 25% of its iPhones in India, minister says
entries.description: India's minister of commerce and industry said Apple is looking to make 25% of all iPhones in India, up from between 5%-7% currently.

entries.title: We'll need natural gas for years — but can start blending it with green hydrogen today, CEO says
entries.description: Andrés Gluski made his comments during a panel discussion at the World Economic Forum in Davos, Switzerland.

entries.title: Treasury yields hold steady as investors assess monetary policy outlook
entries.description: U.S. Treasury yields were little changed Monday as investors mulled the Fed’s next interest rate decision and considered the outlook for the economy.

entries.title: Singapore’s 15 fastest-growing jobs for 2023, according to LinkedIn
entries.description: The growth of AI, increased focus on cybersecurity and continued shift towards digital is leading to growth in technical jobs across Asia, said LinkedIn.
